The paper presents a framework for data-driven robotics that involves learning reward functions and using batch reinforcement learning to train agents to perform manipulation tasks. This work is highly relevant to the field of robotics (cs.RO) and involves machine learning techniques such as batch reinforcement learning (cs.LG) and learning reward functions (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves object manipulation tasks that may require computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and the use of a real robot platform suggests a systems and control perspective (cs.SY).
